P. and M. Curie-Paris 6 University
LIP6 Laboratory
PEQUAN Team


 
To install the library, follow the instructions in the INSTALL file.

Some examples :

./configure FC=YourC++Compiler 
./configure --prefix=TheInstallationDirectory
./configure --enable-64bit
./configure FC=YourC++Compiler  --prefix=TheInstallationDirectory --enable-64bit

Then 
make install

Then, to compile and execute some test examples, just do:


cd examples
make clean 
make


Remarks : 

Under Linux computer with Intel  and  icpc (Intel C++ Compiler), use a command line like : 

./configure FC=icpc  --prefix=TheInstallationDirectory --enable-64bit


